hares  of apple worth  billion by the end of june  this stake had increased to  million shares  of apple berkshire then restarted buying apple stock again between september to december by  december  berkshire had built up a stake of  million shares  of apple with an estimated blended acquisition price of  per share aggressive stock purchases continued and by  march  berkshire had amassed a stake of  million shares  of apple in media reports buffett says that apple has developed an ecosystem and level of brand loyalty that provides it with a competitive moat and that consumers appear to have a degree of price insensitivity when it comes to the iphone investments in us airlinesedit in  berkshire surprised investors by making large equity investments in the major us airlines buffett had previously described airlines as a deathtrap for investors buffett had made an investment in us airways in  which although he sold for a profit almost lost berkshire a substantial sum of money as of  berkshire is currently the largest shareholder in united airlines and delta air lines and a top  shareholder in southwest airlines and american airlines buffett himself has described this as a call on the industry rather than a choice in an individual company american airlines ceo doug parker is said to have won over ted weschler in arguing that the airline industry had consolidated sufficiently and rationalised supply such that longer term profitability could be achieved in an industry that has historically been loss making in aggregate prior investmentsedit berkshire previously held a considerable stake in tesco plc the uk grocery retailer berkshire made its first investment in tesco in  and in  raised this stake to over  of the company with a cost for the investment of  billion buffett sold around  of this stake in  when he “soured somewhat on the company’s thenmanagement” realising a profit of  million as tescos problems mounted through  berkshire sold all the remaining shares with buff